===Etymology===
Popularized by Pierre Bézier.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=Bézier [[curve]]}}

# {{mathematics}} A [[parametric]] curve defined by a set of [[control point]]s, two of which are the ends of the curve, and the others determine its shape. Bézier curves are applied e.g. in [[computer graphics]] to produce smooth, infinitely scalable curves.

